[4] Canada (Nunavut): dog, unknown human exp
Date: Thu 11 Aug 2022 15:07 EDT
Source: Nunatsiaq News [edited]
https://nunatsiaq.com/stories/article/gn-warns-of-possible-rabies-case-in-kugluktuk/


The Department of Health is warning of potential case of rabies in Kugluktuk after a dog died showing "possible signs" of the disease, according to a news release. Anyone who is bitten or scratched by a dog or a fox should go to the local health centre, seek treatment and report the incident immediately, as rabies infections are almost always fatal, states the release.

It also says people who tie up their dogs outside should monitor their animals for behaviours which could indicate possible rabies signs. That includes staggering, frothing at the mouth, choking or making strange noises.

Anybody who sees a fox or wolf wandering around the community can contact Kugluktuk's conservation officer. Anybody whose dog has had contact with a fox or wolf can contact the regional environmental health officer.

